### Component: API Routes

#### [NEW] `src/app/api/blog/route.ts`
```
GET  /api/blog          → Lista posts publicados
POST /api/blog          → Cria novo post (auth required)
```

#### [NEW] `src/app/api/blog/[id]/route.ts`
```
GET    /api/blog/:id    → Busca post por ID
PUT    /api/blog/:id    → Atualiza post (auth required)
DELETE /api/blog/:id    → Deleta post (auth required)
```

#### [NEW] `src/app/api/leads/route.ts`
```
POST /api/leads → Salva lead capturado pelo formulário
GET  /api/leads → Lista leads (auth required)
```

#### [NEW] `src/app/api/analytics/track/route.ts`
```
POST /api/analytics/track → Registra pageview (chamado pelo middleware)
```

#### [NEW] `src/app/api/analytics/dashboard/route.ts`
```
GET /api/analytics/dashboard → Retorna métricas agregadas
```

#### [NEW] `src/middleware.ts`
- Protege as rotas `/admin/*`
- Injeta tracking de pageview em todas as rotas públicas
- Lê cookies de sessão para autenticação

---

### Lib: Camada de Dados

#### [NEW] `src/lib/db/posts.ts`
Funções CRUD para posts (inicialmente com JSON local, migra para Supabase na Fase 2).

#### [NEW] `src/lib/db/leads.ts`
Funções CRUD para leads.

#### [NEW] `src/lib/db/analytics.ts`
Funções de leitura/escrita de analytics.

#### [NEW] `src/lib/auth/session.ts`
Login simples com senha hardcoded (admin panel) + JWT cookie.

---

### Package Dependencies

Novos pacotes necessários:
```bash
npm install @supabase/supabase-js recharts react-markdown @uiw/react-md-editor jose date-fns
```

- **recharts** — gráficos do dashboard
- **react-markdown** — preview de markdown no editor
- **@uiw/react-md-editor** — editor markdown rico
- **jose** — JWT para autenticação
- **date-fns** — formatação de datas
- **@supabase/supabase-js** — Fase 2 (pronto para instalar)

